14/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A week-long NATO exercise involving troops and equipment from 14 member states and partners started off Croatia's Adriatic coast on Saturday (13 September). The manoeuvres are focused on rescue at sea and on mine-clearing. Taking part are 500 troops, along with ships and planes from Belgium, France, Greece, Italy, Bulgaria, Romania, Slovenia, Latvia, Albania, Croatia, Russia, Ukraine, Egypt and Algeria. (AFP - 13/09/03)
